This paper is about improving language models, which falls under the category of natural language processing (NLP). Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the use of stochastic gradient descent (SGD) and achieving state-of-the-art results, which are topics related to machine learning. Hence, cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) are also likely sub-categories. The paper also mentions the use of neural networks, which is a common technique in deep learning, and therefore cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is another possible sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses the use of language models for text data, which is a common application in computer vision, and therefore cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is a less likely but still possible sub-category.
